\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Choosing the context bound $N$, swept on all five logs ($\tau {=}5$, $K{=}1$). (a) MAE to R1 plateaus from $N{\approx }4$ on every log; $N{=}6$ is optimal on L1 and within $0.004$ on L2--L4. (b) The realized per-step mutation rate rises monotonically with $N$ on every log (log scale) and offers no maximum, so calibration, not novelty, fixes $N$. The band marks the chosen $N{=}6$.}}{17}{figure.1.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:nsweep}{{6}{17}{Choosing the context bound $N$, swept on all five logs ($\tau {=}5$, $K{=}1$). (a) MAE to R1 plateaus from $N{\approx }4$ on every log; $N{=}6$ is optimal on L1 and within $0.004$ on L2--L4. (b) The realized per-step mutation rate rises monotonically with $N$ on every log (log scale) and offers no maximum, so calibration, not novelty, fixes $N$. The band marks the chosen $N{=}6$}{figure.1.6}{}}
