\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Per-method calibration against the cross-validation ground truth R1 across all five logs (six non-degenerate miners per log, up to 30 points, one marker per log; dashed line $y{=}x$). The generative and resampling metrics (M1 ShadowGen, M6adapted) sit on the line on every log; the published Entropia \texttt  {-bgen} F-measure of the same bootstrap sample (M6original) sits far below it (its F1 folds precision in, Sect.\nobreakspace  {}\ref {sec:eval:m6}); M2 PM4Py forms a flat band that ignores the ground-truth gradient; M5 AVATAR (shown off-protocol on L1/L2 only, Sect.\nobreakspace  {}\ref {sec:eval:feasibility}) and M7 SpeciAL scatter off the line. Metrics that could not run on every log appear with fewer points: AVATAR's sparse panel is itself the feasibility verdict.}}{21}{figure.1.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:calibration}{{7}{21}{Per-method calibration against the cross-validation ground truth R1 across all five logs (six non-degenerate miners per log, up to 30 points, one marker per log; dashed line $y{=}x$). The generative and resampling metrics (M1 ShadowGen, M6adapted) sit on the line on every log; the published Entropia \texttt {-bgen} F-measure of the same bootstrap sample (M6original) sits far below it (its F1 folds precision in, Sect.~\ref {sec:eval:m6}); M2 PM4Py forms a flat band that ignores the ground-truth gradient; M5 AVATAR (shown off-protocol on L1/L2 only, Sect.~\ref {sec:eval:feasibility}) and M7 SpeciAL scatter off the line. Metrics that could not run on every log appear with fewer points: AVATAR's sparse panel is itself the feasibility verdict}{figure.1.7}{}}
